[msg TUTORIAL_MSG01 [Ailments]]
[s][clr 2]Ailments[clr 27] are abnormal negative statuses, usually[n]bearing drawbacks for a period of affliction.[n]The ailments are as follows:[n][w][e]

[msg TUTORIAL_MSG02 [Ailments]]
[s][clr 2]Burn[clr 27]: Receive damage after acting.[n][clr 2]Freeze[clr 27]: Cannot act.[n][clr 2]Shock[clr 27]: Cannot act, and may electrocute others [n]around you.[n][w][e]

[msg TUTORIAL_MSG03 [Ailments]]
[s][clr 2]Dizzy[clr 27]: Accuracy greatly reduced.[n][clr 2]Forget[clr 27]: Cannot use skills.[n][clr 2]Sleep[clr 27]: Cannot act, but HP and SP will slowly recover[n]over time.[n][w][e]

[msg TUTORIAL_MSG04 [Ailments]]
[s][clr 2]Confuse[clr 27]: Take actions that will be disadvantageous[n]to your party.[n][clr 2]Fear[clr 27]: High chance of ignoring commands.[n]May flee from battle.[n][w][e]

[msg TUTORIAL_MSG05 [Ailments]]
[s][clr 2]Despair[clr 27]: Cannot act and SP decreases over time.[n]Eventually leads to death.[n][clr 2]Rage[clr 27]: Increases attack, but lowers defense. [n]Can only use melee attacks.[n][w][e]

[msg TUTORIAL_MSG06 [Ailments]]
[s][clr 2]Brainwash[clr 27]: Attack allies and buff or heal enemies.[n][clr 2]Hunger[clr 27]: Greatly lowers the power of all attacks.[n][w][e]

